%TAG !u! tag:unity3d.com,2011:
--- !u!114 &11400000
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 55fc01baa0be7b54e8ef6801bfc93ce6, type: 3}
  m_Name: SheepTwo
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  PromptOneButtonDisplay: 0
  PromptTwoButtonDisplay: 1
  ButtonOneText: Liars
  ButtonTwoText: No Answer
  NormalDialogue:
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: 'You really want to see if what I said is true: that there would be
      no consequence for whom you shoot.'
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: You'd be right. If you decide to shoot another black sheep in the room,
      you won't face any repercussions.
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: Well, that's great to hear. Maybe next round you'll be my next victim.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: ...
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: ...However, there are always motives behind the actions we take. What
      are yours for shooting a random person?
  ButtonOneDialogue:
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: I wish you'd stop talking already. Are all dealers secret interrogators?
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: Whatever. Like I give a damn. We'll forget each other soon enough.
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: People lie. It's natural to lie when you want to protect yourself or
      others.
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: Then there are those who consistently lie.
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: They make you believe in something, then later lie before trying to
      retract their statement.
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: When you realize they've lied to you, you become curious about how many
      lies they've told before.
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: Then trust breaks. Trust is disposable.
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: If done by multiple people, then where's the line separating reality
      from falsehood?
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: That said, people also talk behind your back all the time. I don't think
      people realize it, but I'm not dumb. I know people love drama, love to hate,
      love to lie.
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: 'Ha, people will find anything to hate anyone, and anyone will find
      anything to hate me too. '
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: People inherently want to lie, so if I have the choice not to be lied
      to, I'll take it.
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: Of course, you can ignore all this garbage I've said. It doesn't matter
      because we don't know each other.
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: This is just a fleeting encounter, anyway...
  - CharacterTitle: 0
    Message: They pull more wool off their arm as the stinging sensation worsens.
  - CharacterTitle: 0
    Message: The creature takes the wool and moves it underneath the table.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: ' ...I''ll start a new round.'
  ButtonTwoDialogue:
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: Motives? Really? Using that word? I sound like a criminal.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: It was the best word I could think of.
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: I'm not telling you my resentment toward people.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: So it's resentment for others?
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: Sure, but do whatever with that fact. Everyone loves to assume anyway.
  - CharacterTitle: 0
    Message: They pull more wool off their arm as the stinging sensation worsens.
  - CharacterTitle: 0
    Message: The creature takes the wool and moves it underneath the table.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: I'll start a new round.
